summary: I don't care if J.K. Rowling said it. She can't say all racists are Slytherins.
body:
I don’t care if J.K. Rowling said it. She can’t say all racists are Slytherins.

Too long; won’t read: racism and house discrimination are both discrimination, and all the other three houses discriminated slytherins and stereotyped them as evil.

She can’t just dump all the racists in the Slytherin house, and I’ll tell you why. No over analyzing house values or anything. Just one example that is seen in all the books and movies.

House discrimination. That’s it. I mean, isn’t racism and house discrimination sort of the same at the core? Discriminating and giving horrible stereotypes to a group of people. You’re black? You’re stupid. You’re a slytherin? You’re evil. And it’s obvious that there were a lot of people in the books who were cautious of slytherins because of the stereotypes.

I admit, it’s less likely that ravenclaws and hufflepuffs are racists because they value individuality and equality, and I should mention I’m not saying that gryffindors alone discriminate slytherins.

Also, if there is anything I said that is wrong, please correct me, but also please be polite about it.

Thank you for coming to my TED talk.
